              "free_text": [
                " The natural Li foil with a thickness of 3.7",
                " mg/cm2 was sandwiched between two tantalum foils of",
                " different thicknesses.",
                "The front tantalum foil was of thickness 3.9 mg/cm2",
                " and the back tantalum foil is thicker than 0.025 mm,",
                " which was sufficient to stop the proton beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Mo metal foil (0.2916 g at 11.9 MeV and 0.0490 g",
                " at 14.75 MeV) was wrapped with 0.025 mm thick Al",
                " foil.",
                "The chemically pure (99.99%) Au and In metal foils of",
                " 0.0324 and 0.0737 g weight were wrapped separately",
                " with 0.025 mm thick Al foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The samples were irradiated for 7-11 hours with",
                "a neutron beam. The irradiated samples of In, Au and Mo",
                "were cooled for 1.12-2.43, 149.33-243.2 and 97.65-",
                "192.5 hours, respectively for different sets of",
                "measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross sections have been corrected by removing the",
                "contribution due to the tail part of the neutron",
                "spectra. The folding of cross-sections from TALYS with",
                "neutron flux distributions was done by using the",
                "neutron spectrum."
              ]
            }
